oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Autogenous Bacterins
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Brown, Ned
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: I am supposed to talk about atuogenous bacterins and I can understand what an autogenous bacterin can be in a bunch of ten or 12 calves or a dairy herd of I 00 or 150 cows, but I do not know where an autogenous bacterin begins and an autogenous bacterin ends in a feedlot with about 30,000 head.
